DOM (Document Object Model):
 --DOM is basically the representation of the same html document but in a tree like
   structure composed of object.
 --Mainly used in web develeopment and used to interact and manipulate(change) 
   the html document.
--When the webpage loaded, the browser create DOM of the webpage
--When html file is loaded into the browser the javascript cannot unsderstand html 
  document directly

  Keypoints:
  1)Structure: -The DOM represents the structure of HTML.
               -Each node in tree represents the elements, an attribute or text

  2)Manipulation: -using javascript, you can interact with elements(buttons,paragraphs) 
                   on the webpage, changing the content, styles can be added or remove elements

  3)Event Handling: - you can handle the interactions, like click or pressing the buttons

  4)W3C: world wide web Consortium

 --Document is the entry point of DOM 



 --Methods of Document Objects:
   -used to interact with & to manipulate the document.
   1) Getting Element:
       a) Getting Element by id 
       b) Getting Element by class
       c) Getting Element by tag
       d) Getting Element by query selector




Eg: using class:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<style>
    .br{
        color: brown;
    }

    .b{
        color: blue;
    }

    .r{
        color: red;
    }
</style>
<body>
    <h1 class="br">Pavani</h1>
    <h1 class="b">Kavya</h1>
    <h1 class="r">Sneha</h1>
    <h1 class="br">Sivani</h1>
    <h1 class="r">Bhanu</h1>
    <h1 class="b">Ramya</h1>

    <!-- pavani & sivani brown
         Sneha & Bhanu in red
         Kavya & Ramya in blue-->

</body>
</html>
